Citation.sAbstract: The paper reports experimental p x data for the ternary system (ethyl 1,1-dimethylethyl ether +  1-hexene + toluene) at T = 313.15 K. The ether, synthesized from ethanol of biological origin, increases  the interest of this compound as an additive for gasolines. An isothermal total pressure cell was used  for the measurements. Data reduction by Barker s method provides correlations for GE, using Wilson,  NRTL, UNIQUAC models and the Wohl expansion for the ternary system and the calculation of the vapor  phase composition. Good results are obtained for the correlation by all the models.
Citation.sTitle: Thermodynamics of fuels with a bio-synthetic component (IV): (Vapor + liquid) equilibrium data for the ternary mixture (ethyl 1,1-dimethylethyl ether + 1-hexene + toluene) at T = 313.15 K
